# BridgeFlow Project Rules

## Project Positioning

BridgeFlow is a human-AI collaboration bridge tool for multi-AI-role teams.

- **Phone side**: Command center (ADMIN01) — send tasks, view status, scan to bind
- **PC side**: Dedicated execution machine — receive tasks, write files, patrol, bridge
- **Relay**: Lightweight text event forwarding layer (wss://your-relay-server/bridgeflow/ws/)

## Naming Conventions

| Name | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `BridgeFlow` | Application-level name |
| `agent_bridge` | File collaboration protocol |
| `bridgeflow` | Python package name / CLI |
| `ADMIN01` | Human operator role |
| `PM01/DEV01/OPS01/QA01` | AI execution roles |

## Directory Structure

```
BridgeFlow/
├── src/bridgeflow/      # Python package — no one-off scripts here
├── web/pwa/             # PWA source — sync to bridgeflow-pwa repo and bump version after changes
├── docs/                # Project docs — update when code changes
├── docs/agents/         # Agent role definitions and task files
├── server/relay/        # Local debug relay (not for production)
└── scripts/             # Operations scripts
```

## Code Standards

### Python
- Minimum version: Python 3.10
- Package management: `pyproject.toml` (no `setup.py`)
- CLI entry: `src/bridgeflow/cli.py`
- Cross-platform: Windows / macOS / Linux

### PWA (web/pwa/)
- Must bump `config.js` `appVersion` on every change, otherwise Service Worker cache won't update
- Sync to `bridgeflow-pwa/` and push to GitHub Pages after changes
- Core functionality must not depend on CDN (CDN only for optional enhancements)

### File Protocol (agent_bridge)
- Task file format: `TASK-YYYYMMDD-sequence-sender-to-recipient.md`
- Every file must have a YAML metadata header (protocol / version / sender / recipient / thread_key)
- Content must not only exist in relay messages without being saved to files

## Relay Event Specification

Outgoing events must include:
```json
{
  "room_key": "...",
  "sender": "ADMIN01",
  "client_type": "mobile_admin",
  "event_type": "...",
  "payload": {}
}
```

## Release Process

### Python Package (PyPI)
1. Update `version` in `pyproject.toml`
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md`
3. Build: `py -3.10 -m build`
4. Upload: `py -3.10 -m twine upload dist/*`

### PWA (GitHub Pages)
1. Update `appVersion` in `web/pwa/config.js`
2. Sync: `Copy-Item ..\web\pwa\index.html index.html -Force` (in `bridgeflow-pwa/` directory)
3. Push: `git push origin main`

## Prohibited Actions

- Do not hardcode real `room_key` in public example configs
- Do not transmit large files via relay (8KB limit)
- Do not modify existing task files in `docs/agents/tasks/` and `reports/` (append only)
- Do not introduce a secondary "chat-only, no-file" protocol
